Fiat, Peugeot Cut Prices to Win Share From VW, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-09-06T06:39:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/fiat-peugeot-cut-prices-to-win-share-from-vw-handelsblatt-says.html
Fiat SpA (F)  and PSA Peugeot Citroen are
cutting prices in  Germany  to try to win market share from
 Volkswagen AG (VOW) ,  Handelsblatt said , citing the Center for
Automotive Research.  Importers sold 18 models in August with discounts of more
than 25 percent, the highest number with such a large rebate in
Germany since January 2010, the newspaper said, citing a
discount index published by the research center, located at the
 University of Duisburg-Essen .  Italyâ€™s Fiat sold Panda and Punto cars for 35 percent and
31 percent less respectively, while Paris-based Peugeot gave
discounts of about 30 percent on Citroen Berlingo, C1 and C3
models through leasing agreements, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
